# 🕌 Islamic RAG System

A full-stack Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) system for answering Islamic questions using authentic sources from IslamQA.

---

## 🚀 Overview

This project builds an end-to-end AI system that:

- Scrapes and processes thousands of Islamic Q&A (fatwas)
- Converts them into structured, meaningful chunks
- Embeds them using modern embedding models
- Stores them in a vector database (Pinecone)
- Retrieves relevant context for user queries
- Generates grounded answers using an LLM

---

## 🧠 Architecture

```text
User Query
    ↓
Embedding (OpenAI)
    ↓
Pinecone Vector Search
    ↓
Top-k Relevant Chunks
    ↓
Context Builder
    ↓
LLM (RAG Prompt)
    ↓
Final Answer
```

---

## 📦 Project Structure

```text
islamic-rag/
│
├── ingestion/              # Scraping IslamQA sitemap + pages
│
├── processing/             # Data processing pipelines
│   ├── chunker.py          # Structure-aware chunking
│   ├── embedder.py         # Embedding logic
│   ├── run_chunking.py     # Chunking pipeline
│   ├── run_embeddings.py   # Embedding pipeline
│
├── db/                     # Vector DB (Pinecone)
│   ├── pinecone_client.py
│   ├── create_index.py
│   ├── upsert_vectors.py
│   ├── query.py
│
├── rag/                    # RAG pipeline
│   ├── retriever.py        # Retrieves relevant chunks
│   ├── prompt_builder.py   # Builds context for LLM
│   ├── generator.py        # Generates final answer
│
├── data/                   # (ignored) raw + processed data
├── .env
├── README.md
```

---

## ⚙️ Features

### 🔹 Data Pipeline

- Async scraping from IslamQA sitemap
- Structured parsing (title, question, answer, metadata)
- JSONL-based streaming pipeline

### 🔹 Chunking

- Paragraph-based chunking (not naive token splitting)
- Section-aware (handles I, II, III when present)
- Context-enriched chunks (title + question included)

### 🔹 Embeddings

- OpenAI `text-embedding-3-large`
- Batch processing for efficiency
- ~100k+ chunks embedded

### 🔹 Vector Database

- Pinecone (serverless)
- Cosine similarity search
- Metadata filtering support

### 🔹 RAG Pipeline

- Top-k retrieval
- Context construction
- Controlled LLM prompting
- Reduced hallucination via source grounding

---

## 🛠️ Setup

### 1. Clone repo

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/islamic-rag.git
cd islamic-rag
```

---

### 2. Install dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

### 3. Set environment variables

Create `.env`:

```env
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_key
PINECONE_API_KEY=your_key
```

---

### 4. Create Pinecone index

```bash
python db/create_index.py
```

---

### 5. Run pipelines

```bash
# Chunking
python processing/run_chunking.py

# Embeddings
python processing/run_embeddings.py

# Upload to Pinecone
python db/upsert_vectors.py
```

---

## 🔍 Example Usage

```python
from rag.generator import generate_answer

query = "Is giving lessons after prayer allowed?"
answer = generate_answer(query)

print(answer)
```

---

## 📊 Data Scale

- ~15,000+ fatwas
- ~39,000+ chunks
- ~30M+ tokens embedded
- <$1 embedding cost

---

## ⚠️ Limitations

- Retrieval quality depends on chunking + embedding quality
- No reranking yet (planned)
- No UI (planned React frontend)
- Limited evaluation benchmarks

---

## 🔮 Future Improvements

- 🔥 Reranking layer (major quality boost)
- Hybrid search (semantic + keyword)
- Chunk expansion
- FastAPI backend
- React frontend UI
- Evaluation framework (accuracy testing)

---

## 🧠 Key Learnings

- Chunking quality matters more than model choice
- Metadata design is critical for retrieval
- RAG systems fail silently without evaluation
- Simpler architectures (like Pinecone) speed up iteration

